@startuml partition-layout
title Parallel matrix: row partitioning and per thread storage

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundCorner 6
skinparam objectBackgroundColor #FDFDFD

object "parallel_matrix" as PM {
    n_rows    = 10000
    n_cols    = 10000
    n_threads = 4
    pool      = thread_pool(4)
}

object "partition[0]" as P0 {
    row_start = 0
    row_end   = 2500
    rows      = vector<row>[2500]
    csr       = csr_storage (local)
    dirty     = bitset[2500]
}

object "partition[1]" as P1 {
    row_start = 2500
    row_end   = 5000
    rows      = vector<row>[2500]
    csr       = csr_storage (local)
    dirty     = bitset[2500]
}

object "partition[2]" as P2 {
    row_start = 5000
    row_end   = 7500
    rows      = vector<row>[2500]
    csr       = csr_storage (local)
    dirty     = bitset[2500]
}

object "partition[3]" as P3 {
    row_start = 7500
    row_end   = 10000
    rows      = vector<row>[2500]
    csr       = csr_storage (local)
    dirty     = bitset[2500]
}

object "worker[0]\n(jthread)" as W0
object "worker[1]\n(jthread)" as W1
object "worker[2]\n(jthread)" as W2
object "worker[3]\n(jthread)" as W3

PM o-- P0
PM o-- P1
PM o-- P2
PM o-- P3

W0 ..> P0 : owns during execute()
W1 ..> P1
W2 ..> P2
W3 ..> P3

note bottom of PM
    Row ownership (routing): owner(r) = r * n_threads / n_rows
    Partition boundaries recomputed by rebalance() using
    an NNZ-balanced prefix-sum + binary search.
end note

note right of P0
    Each partition owns:
      - its row objects (buffers + index maps)
      - its own csr_storage
      - its own dirty bitset
    Partitions are disjoint;
    no data is shared across threads.
end note

@enduml
